title: Outgoing email for Thunderbird
buttons: conclude: Yes, problememailticket: No

<p>Okay, we need to make sure your outgoing email settings are correct.</p>

<ol>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Tools</strong> menu, then select <strong>Account Settings</strong></li>
    <li>Click on <strong>Outgoing Server (SMTP)</strong></li>
    <li>Select the server in the box and click <strong>Edit</strong></li>
    <li>The SMTP server should be <strong>volomail.net</strong></li>
    <li>The port number should be <strong>587</strong></li>
    <li>The box next to "Use name and password" under "Security and Authentication" should be checked.</li>
</ol>

<p>Can you try sending an email now?</p>

<p class="dont-say">Wait for the caller to try it out...</p>

<p>Did that fix the problem?</p>

